#: src/2128-use-nested-groups.md:103
msgid ""
"Resolution:  \n"
"First the import tree is prefixed with `::`, unless it already starts with "
"`::`, `self` or `super`.  \n"
"Then resolution is performed as if the whole import tree were flattened, "
"except that `{self}`/`{self as name}` are processed specially because `a::b::"
"self` is illegal."
msgstr ""

