#: src/2128-use-nested-groups.md:140
msgid ""
"This RFC is an incremental improvement largely independent from other import-"
"related proposals, but it can have effect on some other RFCs."
msgstr ""

#: src/2128-use-nested-groups.md:143
msgid ""
"Some RFCs propose new syntaxes for absolute paths in the current crate and "
"paths from other crates. Some arguments in those proposals are based on "
"usage statistics - \"imports from other crates are more common\" or "
"\"imports from the current crate are more common\". More common imports are "
"supposed to get less verbose syntax."
msgstr ""

#: src/2128-use-nested-groups.md:149
msgid ""
"This RFC removes the these statistics from the equation by reducing "
"verbosity for all imports with common prefix.  \n"
"For example, the difference in verbosity between `A`, `B` and `C` is minimal "
"and doesn't depend on the number of imports."
msgstr ""

